  - {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8c531e326c26c8440bb9999ecf17f41c, type: 2}
  Description: "Gnomes are short and hardy folk, with an unquenchable curiosity and
    eccentric habits.\r\n\r\nLong ago, early gnome ancestors emigrated from the First
    World, realm of the fey. While it's unclear why the first gnomes wandered to
    Golarion, this lineage manifests in modern gnomes as bizarre reasoning, eccentricity,
    obsessive tendencies, and what some see as naivete.\r\n\r\nAlways hungry for
    new experiences, gnomes constantly wander both mentally and physically, attempting
    to stave off a terrible ailment that threatens all of their people. This affliction,
    known as the Bleaching, strikes gnomes who fail to dream, innovate, and take
    in new experiences. The Bleaching slowly drains the color\u2014 literally\u2014from
    gnomes, and it plunges those affected into states of deep depression that eventually
    claim their lives. Very few gnomes survive this scourge, becoming deeply morose
    and wise survivors known as bleachlings.\r\n\r\nIf you want a character with
    boundless enthusiasm and an alien, fey outlook on morality and life, you should
    play a gnome."
  Hitpoints: 8
  Size: 1
  Speed: 25
